Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic properties of ionic liquid, 1-hexyl-3-methylimidazolum  bromide, + N-N'bis(2-pyridylmethylidene)-1,2-diiminoethane(BPIE) Schiff  base + N,N- dimethylformamide solutions at T = (298.15 to 313.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Effect of N-N'bis(2-pyridylmethylidene)-1,2-diiminoethane (BPIE) Schiff base on  thermodynamic properties of ionic liquid, 1-hexyl-3-methylimidazolium bromide  ([HMIm]Br) in N,N-dimethylformamide (DMF) solutions were determined at T = (298.15 K  to 313.15) K. The standard partial molar volumes, 0 V O , partial molar volumes of  transfer, 0  trV O  ' , have been calculated using density data. The cosphere overlap model was  used to interpretate partial molar volumes of transfer, 0  trV O  ' ,.The calculated Hepler's  constants, 2 0 2 V / T  O  g  g , indicate that ionic liquid are structure-breaking (chaotropic). Ion  association constants, a K , and limiting molar conductivities, 0  1/4 , viscosity B-coefficients and  molar refractions, RD, have been used to confirm the conclusions obtained from the  volumetric properties. The results were interpreted in terms of solute-solvent interactions and  indicating an enhancement in the nonpolar!Vnonpolar interactions between the BPIE Schiff  base and the ionic liquid.
